Interface BaseAcscNetwork<TBus extends BaseAcscBus<? extends AcscGen,? extends AcscLoad>,TBranch extends AcscBranch>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseAclfNetwork<TBus,TBranch>, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAclfAreaZone, IAclfNetAdjustment, IAclfNetElement, IAclfNetFormMatrix, IAclfNetFunc, IAdaptable, IMultiNet, INet3WXfrElement, INetBranchElement<TBus,TBranch>, INetBusElement<TBus>, INetworkElement, NameTag, Network<TBus,TBranch>, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AcscNetworkImpl, BaseAcscNetworkImpl, BaseDStabNetworkImpl, DStabilityNetworkImpl, Dynamic3PNetworkImpl, Steady3PNetworkImpl

    public interface BaseAcscNetwork<TBus extends BaseAcscBus<? extends AcscGen,? extends AcscLoad>,TBranch extends AcscBranch>
extends BaseAclfNetwork<TBus,TBranch>
    A representation of the model object 'Base Acsc Network'. * ACSCNetwork * Notes 1) for L-G fault, zeq = zdd0 + zdd2, i1 = i2 = i0 * for L-L fault, zeq = zdd2, i2 = -i1, i0=0 * for LL-G fault, zeq = zdd0 || zdd2; i2 and i0 calcualted based * on v1 on the fault point * 2) For 3-phase fault a zfualt can be defined, but for other types of * faults, zfault = 0.0

    The following features are supported:

    • Sc Data Loaded
    • Positive Seq Data Only
    • Zero Seq YMatrix
    • Neg Seq YMatrix
    See Also:
    AcscPackage.getBaseAcscNetwork()
